<p>I'm trying to get started with kafka and the kafka-python module. I followed this guide in order to set a very basic consumer and producer:</p>  <p><a href="http://www.giantflyingsaucer.com/blog/?p=5541" rel="nofollow">http://www.giantflyingsaucer.com/blog/?p=5541</a></p>  <p>Everything works nicely, I can create some message with the producer and then I can consume them with the consumer. I'm now trying to consume the messages creating some processes following the documentation so basically using this code:</p>  <p><a href="http://kafka-python.readthedocs.org/en/latest/usage.html#multiprocess-consumer" rel="nofollow">http://kafka-python.readthedocs.org/en/latest/usage.html#multiprocess-consumer</a></p>  <pre><code>from kafka import KafkaClient, MultiProcessConsumer  kafka = KafkaClient('localhost:9092')  # This will split the number of partitions among two processes consumer = MultiProcessConsumer(kafka, b'my-group', b'my-topic', num_procs=2)  # This will spawn processes such that each handles 2 partitions max consumer = MultiProcessConsumer(kafka, b'my-group', b'my-topic', partitions_per_proc=2)                    for message in consumer:     print(message)  for message in consumer.get_messages(count=5, block=True, timeout=4):     print(message) </code></pre>  <p>But the errors I'm receiving are the following:</p>  <pre><code>Traceback (most recent call last):   File "consumer.py", line 23, in &lt;module&gt;     consumer = MultiProcessConsumer(kafka, b'my-group', b'test2', partitions_per_proc=2)   File "/home/vdelmeglio/Desktop/kafka_test/python_kafka_test/kafka-test/lib/python3.4/site-packages/kafka/consumer/multiprocess.py", line 162, in __init__     chunks = [partitions[proc::num_procs] for proc in range(num_procs)] TypeError: 'float' object cannot be interpreted as an integer Error in atexit._run_exitfuncs: Traceback (most recent call last):   File "/home/vdelmeglio/Desktop/kafka_test/python_kafka_test/kafka-test/lib/python3.4/site-packages/kafka/consumer/b